titlestmt.titleproper:
Guide to the New York University Archives Collection of Faculty Publications,
1844-1994
RG.1.1
titlestmt.author: Collection processed by Janet Bunde and Eva McCausland.

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace 2023-06-13T13:41:12

did.unittitle: New York University Archives Collection of Faculty Publications
did.physloc: Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please request materials at least two business days prior to your research visit to coordinate access.
did.abstract: The items in this collection represent a sample of published works by New York University professors and lecturers.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Works were boxed in approximate alphabetical order by author's last name. The files are grouped into one series:

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: This collection is housed in 29 boxes, which can contain anywhere from 9 to 24 items. Materials range in publication date from 1844 to 1994, with the bulk of documents in the early to mid-twentieth century. The various publications cover all manner of topics in the humanities, social sciences, physical sciences, and other fields. A brief listing includes history, economics, religion, mathematics, politics and political science, physics, and sociology, although there are many more. Most of the documents included in this collection are articles and books concerning these fields and others, but there are a large number of biographies of various people. Documents are not organized chronologically, thematically, or alphabetically.

The following list displays some of the authors which appear often in this collection. Their works do not make up the majority of the collection, but their names are more prevalent:
Marshall W. Baldwin
Mary Elizabeth Barnicle
William Allen Butler
Elmer Elsworth Brown
Gay Wilson Allen
Henry M. Baird
Henry Pratt Fairchild
John William Draper
Thomas C. Cochran
Abraham I. Katsh
Henry Mitchell MacCracken
William H. Stahl
Ernest G. Sihler
Myron W. Watkins

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: New York University is an academic institution and, as such, its faculty produces articles and books in their respective fields. This collection is an assortment of writings created by various people from multiple fields, indicating the extensive academic work completed by scholars throughout NYU's history. Maintaining these writings fulfills the mission statement of the University Archives in two ways: first, by providing a final repository for NYU-related records, and second, by documenting the intellectual history of the University through the physical preservation of materials.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Published citations should take the following form: Identification of item, date (if known); New York University Archives Collection of Faculty Publications; RG 1.1; box number; folder number; New York University Archives, New York University Libraries.

userestrict.head: Use Restrictions
userestrict.p: Materials in this collection which were created prior to 1924 are in the public domain. Permission to publish or reproduce is not required. Materials that were published in 1924 or later are potentially protected by copyright and/or related rights. You are free to use materials in the collection in any way that is permitted by the copyright and related rights legislation that applies to your use. For other uses you need to obtain permission from the rights-holder(s).
